CommonFields.Title: Functionalisation effect on the thermo-mechanical behaviour of multi-wall carbon nanotube/epoxy-composites
Author: Gojny, Florian H.
Schulte, Karl
CommonFields.Location: Polymer-Composites Section, Technical University Hamburg-Harburg, Denickestrasse 15, 21073 Hamburg, Germany

ChooseParameter.Other: The functionalised nanotubes were purified by oxidation and have amino- groups implemented on the surface.

Mixing.Description: The nanotubes were manually mixed into the hardener.
The sample is cooled in a water bath during the sonication process.

ChooseParameter.Other: The composites were cured for 5 h at 80 °C.

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: films with a thickness of 50 nm were prepared by ultra- microtome cutting

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.Description: The sample were coated with a thin gold layer of 5 nm thickness.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: The tests were performed in tensile mode at a frequency of 10 Hz with a static strain of 0.6% and a dynamic strain of 􏰍0.1%, in a temperature range between )120 and 150 °C with a heating rate of 3 °C/min.

Differential_Scanning_Calorimetry.Description: The samples were measured between –50 and 300 °C.

ImageFile.Description: functionalised nanotubes dispersed directly in the curing agent
functionalised nanotubes dispersed using an additional solvent

SampleSize.description: For the measurements rectangular specimens of 50 mm length, 5 mm width and 2 mm thickness were prepared.
